cs.LG, cs.CE, cs.AI, cs.DB, cs.NE 

The paper uses machine learning techniques (MLP and RNNs) to predict Acute Kidney Injury (AKI) in hospitalized patients using serum creatinine (sCr) as a lone feature. This falls under the broad category of machine learning (cs.LG) and specifically, the sub-categories of computational epidemiology (cs.CE) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as the paper deals with predicting a medical condition using machine learning. The paper also deals with data management and processing, which falls under the sub-category of databases (cs.DB). Finally, the paper uses neural networks, which falls under the sub-category of neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
